      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To test for nitrogen deficiency, look for yellowing leaves, especially on younger ones. You can also conduct a soil test, which will give you a detailed report on nutrient levels, including nitrogen. If it's acidic, add lime to raise the pH, but be careful not to overdo it. If the soil is too alkaline, you can use sulfur or aluminum sulfate to lower the pH. Always follow the instructions on the product label. And remember, it's better to make small adjustments and test again afterward.",
