      "content": "Nitrogen doesn't exactly \"suck\" from plants, but plants use it to grow and it eventually leaves the soil as they decompose. However, if the soil becomes depleted over time without replenishment, the plants can show signs of nitrogen deficiency. Regular fertilizer application or composting can help maintain the nitrogen levels. It's like providing your plants with a steady supply of food to keep them healthy and growing.",
